Step 3: Prepare Documents
Identity Proof: Pan Card or Aadhaar Card.
Address Proof: Driving License or Passport (matching your home address).
Logo Image: A high-resolution JPG of your green "Orgo Foods" logo.
User Affidavit (Optional but Recommended): If you have already started selling, you can claim "Prior Use."
You will need to submit an affidavit with proof (like an invoice or a photo of your packet) showing the date you first used the brand. This strengthens your case.
MSME Certificate: To claim the fee discount.
Step 4: Filing the Application (Form TM-A)
Option A: Do It Yourself (Cheapest)
Where: IP India E-filing Portal.
Requirement: You need a Class 3 Digital Signature Certificate (DSC). Buying a DSC costs about â‚¹1,500â€“â‚¹2,000.
Process: Create an account, fill Form TM-A, upload docs, and pay â‚¹4,500.
Step 5: The Process Timeline
Once you file, you can immediately start using the â„¢ symbol (e.g., Orgo Foodsâ„¢).
Examination (1-3 months): The officer checks your application.
Scenario A: Accepted.
Scenario B: Objection. (They might say "Orgo is too common"). You/your lawyer must file a reply within 30 days.
Publication (3-4 months): Your brand is published in the Trademark Journal. Anyone in India has 4 months to oppose it (e.g., if another company feels you copied them).
Registration: If no one opposes, you get the Â® certificate. You can now use Orgo FoodsÂ®.

